<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">
<span style="FONT-SIZE: 22pt">I Am a Japanese School Teacher</span></b>
<P><h1>*ATTN*</h1>The "I Am a Japanese School Teacher" editorial series has moved 
to <b><a href="http://www.gaijinsmash.net">Gaijin Smash</a></b> as a part of the 
<b><a href="http://www.festeringass.com">Festering Ass Network.</a></b>
<P>There, you will find the same teacher editorials with a new great look and more 
professionalism.  The series will also continue past when my tenure on JET comes to 
an end.
<P><h1>NOTICE</h1> - For those of you worried about new content on <b><a href="http://www.gaijinsmash.net">Gaijin Smash</a></b>,
worry no longer.
<P>It's been almost three years.  ...Do you really think only 117 Editorials could cover it all?
<P>Coming in June to Gaijin Smash, new, never before seen editorials!  "The Lost School Teacher Editorials", 
if you will.  These new entries will chronicles things that have happened over the past three years that 
I have failed to mention...until now.  What could I have possibly left out?  ...You'll see. 
<P>These new editorials will be integrated into the old archives, appearing roughly once 
a week.  Be sure to look for them!
<P>Feel free to stick around <b><a href="../">Outpost Nine</a></b> if you want to 
read more of my works, including editorials on a variety of other subjects, 
fiction, and various pictures (including a lot from my time in Japan).  But for 
more Japan goodness, make sure to head to <b><a href="http://www.gaijinsmash.net">Gaijin Smash</a></b>.
<P>For more information about the move and why it happened, <b><a href="explanation.html">click here.</a></b>


